        "$$y = 1 + \\epsilon$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where $\\epsilon \\sim N(0, \\sigma^2)$.\n",
        "\n",
        "We will consider two models:\n",
        "\n",
        "**Model A** is a linear model with $d=1$ (using an uninformative feature, since $y$ is not a function of any $x$), trained using least squares:\n",
        "\n",
